AGENTS.md
CLAUDE.md
CODE_PRINCIPLES.md
opencode.json
# Planning workspace is local-only, but the LAN-exposure runbook is a shipping
# doc the proxy override depends on (F10). Ignore the tree's CONTENTS (docs/*,
# not docs/ — a dir exclude would block re-inclusion) then carve it back in.
# The Windows-AMD field report is kept local-only (untracked).
docs/*
!docs/lan-exposure.md
# Architecture decision records + the macOS TTS benchmark they cite are the durable,
# versioned decision trail for the native-Kokoro topology — keep them tracked.
!docs/adr/
!docs/macos-tts-benchmark-results.md
design-mockups/
.worktrees/

# Local develop-engine workflow artifacts (never repo content)
WRAP_UP.md
.factory-state/

# Machine-specific live-test compose overrides (header: "LIVE-TEST ONLY").
# The committed docker-compose.*.yml are the shipping topology; these bridge a
# local operator's pre-rename volumes and must stay untracked.
docker-compose.livetest-*.yml
